<div class="ssr-test-page">
    <header class="mb-4">
        <h1>SSR Test Page</h1>
        <p class="text-muted">This page demonstrates server-side rendering</p>
    </header>
    
    <section class="panel">
        <h2 class="mb-3">Server-Side Rendered Content</h2>
        <p style="font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.6;">
            This is content, only rendered via SSR
        </p>
        
        <div class="mt-4 p-3" style="background: var(--surface-light); border-radius: var(--radius-md); border-left: 4px solid var(--success);">
            <p><strong>âœ… SSR Working!</strong></p>
            <p class="text-muted mt-2" style="font-size: 0.875rem;">
                If you can see this content immediately on page load without any client-side JavaScript loading, 
                then server-side rendering is functioning correctly.
            </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="mt-4">
            <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.875rem;">
                <strong>How to verify SSR:</strong><br>
